      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Why Self-Employed Car Loans Can Be Harder</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Lenders need to verify your income to ensure you can afford repayments. For PAYG employees, payslips show consistent income. For self-employed borrowers, income can be variable, seasonal, or structured through a business entity in ways that are less transparent to lenders.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Many self-employed Australians legitimately minimise taxable income through deductions, which can result in tax returns showing lower income than cash actually flowing through the business. This creates a catch-22: strategies that reduce your tax bill can make it harder to prove income to lenders.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Full Doc vs Low Doc Car Loans</h2>
